reviews.title: Disappointing
reviews.text: Good location and reasonable atmosphere inside, but pizza was poor quality. Felt like it has potential to be a nice restaurant but in need of a management refresh.

reviews.title: Good food and service
reviews.text: Very nice food here. The restaurant has a nice and cozy atmosphere. Actually, everything is fine.

reviews.title: A taste of Italy in Friesland
reviews.text: We wanted something a little different, than typical Dutch food, so we stopped in Pizzeria Pompei.  It wasn’t quite the pizza we’ve had in Naples, but much better than most.  Probably the closest to a true Italian pizza in Northern Netherlands. A single pizzeria was enough for two.  The large shrimp appetizer was good, but overpriced.  The beer selection was decent.

reviews.title: Wedding anniversary celebration
reviews.text: We had spent the day cycling round Terschelling to celebrate our 37th anniversary and wanted somewhere good bit casual to celebrate. We found this restaurant by the waters edge. The food was delicious and the service friendly and efficient. We both chose varieties of tortellini and they didn't disappoint. A lovely restaurant would certainly recommend it.

reviews.title: Pizza and beer
reviews.text:
Not a bad tasting pizza, would probably order again. The carpaccio starter was pretty dam good.
The beer is tasty but at 5€ I would expect the glass to be a bit fuller. See below, pretty short measure, a Euro or 2 missing there!

reviews.title: Evening meal with my family
reviews.text: we all had a different freshly made pizza washed down with a nice bottle of Barolla. We could not criticise the restaurant in anyway, the food was very good, the service excellent and the cost moderate. We arrived at 7:30 and by 8:00 it was packed and they were turning peole away so book a place to ensure you are not disappointed.

reviews.title: Pizzas  of vert low quality   Avoid this restaurant
reviews.text: I have rarely eaten such pizzas without flavour and with so low quality components  the only good thing in the restaurant is the service

reviews.title: Very good pizza
reviews.text: Nice pizza for affordable price, for two person pizza, salade and bottle of wine it was around 50 €. Nice terras to breath pure air from the sea.

reviews.title: Superb
reviews.text:
We ate at this pizzeria as a last chance we had to eat at 21:00 and all other restaurants at Harlingen were already closed!
Service was excellent and although we were the last to enter the resto they served us very well!
Food was great, portions huge and prices reasonable!
Menu catalogue was extra large!

articleContent.title: Seneca Village history: The hidden past under Central Park

seoInfo.metaDescription: Beneath Central Park’s concrete pathways and grassy hills are the ruins of Seneca Village, an old African-American settlement. Comprised of homes, two schools, two cemeteries, and three churches, the five acre neighborhood was situated approximately where 82nd and 89th Streets and Seventh and Eighth Avenues are located today.
